page.title: 19GT. WAKERINGS VEGTATION
page.content: MANY SPECIES OF GRASS ARE FOUND ON THE COMMON LAND OF GREAT WAKERING. THESE INCLUDE:- TIMOTHY GRASS, COCKSFOOT, BARLEY GRASS, RYE GRASS, MEADOW FESCUE, COUCH GRASS AND YORKSHIRE FOG. NOT MANY OAK TREES GROW IN THIS AREA. AT ONE TIME THE ELM WAS WIDESPREAD BUT DUE TO THE ONSET OF DUTCH-ELM DISEASE THE NUMBERS HAVE DECREASED. WILLOW TREES SEEM TO BE THE MOST COMMON TREES ON OPEN GROUND, AS WELL AS HAWTHORN AND A FEW ASH. THERE ARE A FEW MAGNIFICENT SPECIMENS OF HORSE CHESTNUT IN AND AROUND THE CHURCH. ALSO IN THE CHURCHYARD ARE YEW.
